      "questionNumber": 40,
      "stem": "A 7 year old boy falls on his outstretched hand. He has pain around the right elbow. X-rays show elevated anterior and posterior fat pads. The capitellum, radial head and trochlea ossification centres are clearly seen, no fracture line is identified. Which of the following is most likely diagnosis?",
