      "stem": "A 3 month old boy presents with irritability, failure to thrive and an unexplained swelling over his right shin. Skeletal Survey reveals periosteal bone thickening in the diaphysis of the right tibia with associated soft tissue swelling. Similar findings are seen in the right clavicle and the left mandible. What is the most likely diagnosis?",
